        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 2:55PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 253 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pueblo West, or 9 miles northwest of Pueblo north of highway 50,
moving southeast at 15 mph. Another strong storm was located 12
miles south southwest of Pueblo, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and brief pea to half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pueblo, Pueblo Airport, Pueblo Reservoir, Salt Creek, Blende, Pueblo
West, Pinon, Avondale, and Colorado City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
